Description: FedNow Service Scope

A retrieval request is the message a FedNow participant uses to request the FedNow Service a copy of one or more messages previously sent or received by the FedNow participant.

FedNow Service Usage

FedNow participants can use the retrieval request to retrieve the following value messages: customer credit transfer (pacs.008), financial institution credit transfer (pacs.009), or payment return (pacs.004). The retrieval request can also be used to retrieve the following nonvalue message: return request (camt.056) and return request response (camt.029), request for payment (pain.013) and request for payment response (pain.014), RFP cancellation request (camt.055) and RFP cancellation request response (camt.029), information request (camt.026), information request response (camt.029) and additional payment information (camt.028).

FedNow participants can use the retrieval request to retrieve messages for the current or prior 7 business days only.

In response to a (successful) message retrieval request, the FedNow Service will deliver a copy of the original message that is being retrieved, e.g., of the original pacs.008 or pain.013 message. The copy of the retrieved message will contain the business application header (head.001) and the ISO 20022 business message (e.g., pacs.008), complemented with a new business application header (head.001) for the retrieved message flow from the FedNow Service to the FedNow participant.

FedNow participants can request the retrieval of up to 50 messages sent or received in a single retrieval request. When a request is made to retrieve multiple messages, the FedNow Service will respond with a separate message for each retrieved message. Depending on the case that individual response will either be the delivery of a copy of a successfully retrieved message, or a message reject (admi.002) for a message that could not be retrieved.

Note: A retrieval request should not be used to request the processing status of a message previously sent through the FedNow Service. To obtain the processing status of a previously sent messages the FedNow participant should use a payment status request (pacs.028). Refer to the customer credit transfer section below for a description of the payment status request message.

